.TH "fpga_mgr_firmware_load" 9 "fpga_mgr_firmware_load" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fpga_mgr_firmware_load \- request firmware and load to fpga
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fpga_mgr_firmware_load
.BI "(struct fpga_manager *mgr "  ","
.BI "struct fpga_image_info *info "  ","
.BI "const char *image_name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mgr" 12
fpga manager
.IP "info" 12
fpga image specific information
.IP "image_name" 12
name of image file on the firmware search path
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Request an FPGA image using the firmware class, then write out to the FPGA.
Update the state before each step to provide info on what step failed if
there is a failure.  This code assumes the caller got the mgr pointer
from \fBof_fpga_mgr_get\fP or \fBfpga_mgr_get\fP and checked that it is not an error
code.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code otherwise.
